{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.19",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 19 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:2",
      "text": "How long will ye vex my soul, and break me in pieces with words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:3",
      "text": "These ten times have ye reproached me: ye are not ashamed that ye make yourselves strange to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:4",
      "text": "And be it indeed that I have erred, mine error remaineth with myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:5",
      "text": "If indeed ye will magnify yourselves against me, and plead against me my reproach:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:6",
      "text": "Know now that God hath overthrown me, and hath compassed me with his net.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:7",
      "text": "Behold, I cry out of wrong, but I am not heard: I cry aloud, but there is no judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:8",
      "text": "He hath fenced up my way that I cannot pass, and he hath set darkness in my paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:9",
      "text": "He hath stripped me of my glory, and taken the crown from my head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:10",
      "text": "He hath destroyed me on every side, and I am gone: and mine hope hath he removed like a tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:11",
      "text": "He hath also kindled his wrath against me, and he counteth me unto him as one of his enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:12",
      "text": "His troops come together, and raise up their way against me, and encamp round about my tabernacle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:13",
      "text": "He hath put my brethren far from me, and mine acquaintance are verily estranged from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:14",
      "text": "My kinsfolk have failed, and my familiar friends have forgotten me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:15",
      "text": "They that dwell in mine house, and my maids, count me for a stranger: I am an alien in their sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:16",
      "text": "I called my servant, and he gave me no answer; I intreated him with my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:17",
      "text": "My breath is strange to my wife, though I intreated for the children’s sake of mine own body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:18",
      "text": "Yea, young children despised me; I arose, and they spake against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:19",
      "text": "All my inward friends abhorred me: and they whom I loved are turned against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:20",
      "text": "My bone cleaveth to my skin and to my flesh, and I am escaped with the skin of my teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:21",
      "text": "Have pity upon me, have pity upon me, O ye my friends; for the hand of God hath touched me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:22",
      "text": "Why do ye persecute me as God, and are not satisfied with my flesh?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:23",
      "text": "Oh that my words were now written! oh that they were printed in a book!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:24",
      "text": "That they were graven with an iron pen and lead in the rock for ever!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:25",
      "text": "For I know that my redeemer liveth, and that he shall stand at the latter day upon the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:26",
      "text": "And though after my skin worms destroy this body, yet in my flesh shall I see God:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:27",
      "text": "Whom I shall see for myself, and mine eyes shall behold, and not another; though my reins be consumed within me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:28",
      "text": "But ye should say, Why persecute we him, seeing the root of the matter is found in me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.19.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:29",
      "text": "Be ye afraid of the sword: for wrath bringeth the punishments of the sword, that ye may know there is a judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
